            <h3>I am a PARENT</h3>
            <b>How will this platform help me?</b>
            <p>Stories are a great resource to keep your children creatively engaged. Reading also helps a child’s development both academically as well personality wise. At StoryWeaver you will find hundreds of stories for children for different reading levels. Also the stories are in multiple languages so your child can read a story in her mother tongue, a language she is trying to learn or just a language she is already proficient in. This is a treasure trove. Dive in.</p>

            <b>How can I know which is the most suitable story for my child?</b>
            <p>Each story will have a badge of the reading level it caters too (Level1, 2,3 or 4). You need to match this to your child’s reading level. To gauge your child’s reading level, know more about it here.</p>

            <b>How do I get my child to read more on StoryWeaver?</b>
            <p>Let your child discover StoryWeaver on her own. Let her look up stories she likes and let her read. Once she finds content she likes, she will automatically read more on StoryWeaver.</p>

            <b>My child loves the stories here and I want to print one of her favorite stories as return gifts for her birthday. How do I do it?</b>
            <p>Such a lovely idea! Please use the download button at the bottom panel of the story detail page to download the story. It will download in a pdf version which you can now print in A4 size sheets.</p>

            <b>I want to talk to other parents and know what their children are reading. How can I?</b>
            <p>You can connect with other users, including other parents via our CONNECT tab. The CONNECT tab will cater to focused discussions as well as get-in-touch requests. Anyone who wants to get in touch with you can do by tagging you at the discussion board.</p>
